Package de.mslab.diffbuilder

Provides helper classes which are required for biclique creation, such as to construct differences for bit-wise or byte-wise operating ciphers, or to compare differentials for their independency.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DifferenceBuilder
    A value builder computes in increasing manner all n-bit/n-byte values with less or equal a maximum number of '1' bits/bytes.
    DifferenceIterator  
    DifferentialBuilder  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractDifferenceIterator  
    AbstractDifferentialBuilder  
    ARIA256DifferenceBuilder
    ARIA-256 uses the round function from the encryption process in its key schedule.
    ARIA256DifferenceIterator  
    BicliqueDifferentialBuilder  
    BitwiseDifferenceBuilder
    Computes in increasing manner all n-bit values with less or equal a maximum number of '1' bit, while all other bits are zero.
    BitwiseDifferenceIterator  
    BKRDifferentialBuilder  
    BytewiseDifferenceBuilder  
    BytewiseDifferenceIterator  
    FullSpaceBytewiseDifferenceBuilder
    Both the BytewiseDifferenceBuilder and the FullSpaceBytewiseDifferenceBuilder classes generate differences for the round key at the starting rounds at the bicliques.
    MatchingDifferentialBuilder  
    NibblewiseDifferenceBuilder
    Computes in increasing manner all n-byte values with less or equal a maximum number of '1' bytes, while all other bytes are zero.
    NibblewiseDifferenceIterator
